\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\CommentTok{\#6.}
\CommentTok{\#The data includes products from five Amazon categories: Automotive, Baby Products, Electronics, Backpacks, and Appliances. It contains product links, descriptions, prices, and average ratings, enabling analysis of pricing and customer satisfaction across these categories.}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\CommentTok{\#7.}
\CommentTok{\#The data helps analyze prices and ratings to identify value{-}for{-}money categories, track market trends, guide customers to affordable, highly{-}rated products, and support businesses in optimizing pricing strategies.}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\CommentTok{\#8.}
\FunctionTok{library}\NormalTok{(ggplot2)}
\FunctionTok{library}\NormalTok{(dplyr)}

\CommentTok{\# Read datasets}
\NormalTok{automotive }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"automotive.csv"}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{babyprod }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"babyprod.csv"}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{electronicsprod }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"electronicsprod.csv"}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{backpacksprod }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"backpacksprod.csv"}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{appliancesprod }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"appliancesprod.csv"}\NormalTok{)}

\CommentTok{\# Combine categories}
\NormalTok{automotive}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Category }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \StringTok{"Automotive"}
\NormalTok{babyprod}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Category }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \StringTok{"Baby Products"}
\NormalTok{electronicsprod}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Category }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \StringTok{"Electronics"}
\NormalTok{backpacksprod}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Category }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \StringTok{"Backpacks"}
\NormalTok{appliancesprod}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Category }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \StringTok{"Appliances"}

\NormalTok{all\_products }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{rbind}\NormalTok{(automotive, babyprod, electronicsprod, backpacksprod, appliancesprod)}

\CommentTok{\# Convert Price and Rating to numeric}
\NormalTok{all\_products}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Price }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as.numeric}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{","}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{, all\_products}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Price))}
\NormalTok{all\_products}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Rating }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as.numeric}\NormalTok{(all\_products}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{Rating)}

\CommentTok{\#Price Distribution}
\FunctionTok{ggplot}\NormalTok{(all\_products, }\FunctionTok{aes}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{x =}\NormalTok{ Category, }\AttributeTok{y =}\NormalTok{ Price, }\AttributeTok{fill =}\NormalTok{ Category)) }\SpecialCharTok{+}
  \FunctionTok{geom\_boxplot}\NormalTok{() }\SpecialCharTok{+}
  \FunctionTok{labs}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{title =} \StringTok{"Price Distribution by Category"}\NormalTok{, }\AttributeTok{x =} \StringTok{"Category"}\NormalTok{, }\AttributeTok{y =} \StringTok{"Price"}\NormalTok{) }\SpecialCharTok{+}
  \FunctionTok{theme\_minimal}\NormalTok{()}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\CommentTok{\#9.}
\CommentTok{\# Load data for each category}
\NormalTok{categories }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{list}\NormalTok{(}
  \StringTok{"Automotive"} \OtherTok{=} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"automotive.csv"}\NormalTok{),}
  \StringTok{"Baby Products"} \OtherTok{=} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"babyprod.csv"}\NormalTok{),}
  \StringTok{"Electronics"} \OtherTok{=} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"electronicsprod.csv"}\NormalTok{),}
  \StringTok{"Backpacks"} \OtherTok{=} \FunctionTok{read.csv}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"backpacksprod.csv"}\NormalTok{),}

\begin{Highlighting}[]
\FunctionTok{library}\NormalTok{(rvest)}
\FunctionTok{library}\NormalTok{(polite)}

\CommentTok{\#product\_1 with reviews}
\CommentTok{\# Define the URL for Automotive category}
\NormalTok{url }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \StringTok{"https://www.amazon.com/s?bbn=2562090011\&rh=n\%3A2562090011\%2Cn\%3A15684181\&dc\&qid=1733043876\&rnid=2941120011\&ref=sr\_nr\_n\_1"}

\NormalTok{session }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ polite}\SpecialCharTok{::}\FunctionTok{bow}\NormalTok{(url, }\AttributeTok{user\_agent =} \StringTok{"Educational"}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{session\_page }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{scrape}\NormalTok{(session)}

\CommentTok{\# Find all div elements with the specified class}
\NormalTok{div\_elements }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{html\_nodes}\NormalTok{(session\_page, }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}div.sg{-}col{-}4{-}of{-}24.sg{-}col{-}4{-}of{-}12.s{-}result{-}item.s{-}asin.sg{-}col{-}4{-}of{-}16.sg{-}col.s{-}widget{-}spacing{-}small.sg{-}col{-}4{-}of{-}20\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}

\CommentTok{\# Create empty vectors to store data}
\NormalTok{product\_data }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{list}\NormalTok{()  }\CommentTok{\# List to store product{-}level data}

\ControlFlowTok{for}\NormalTok{ (div\_element }\ControlFlowTok{in}\NormalTok{ div\_elements) \{}
  \CommentTok{\# Find product link}
\NormalTok{  a\_element }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{html\_node}\NormalTok{(div\_element, }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}a.a{-}link{-}normal.s{-}no{-}outline\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{  link }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{ifelse}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{!}\FunctionTok{is.na}\NormalTok{(a\_element), }\FunctionTok{paste0}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"https://amazon.com"}\NormalTok{, }\FunctionTok{html\_attr}\NormalTok{(a\_element, }\StringTok{"href"}\NormalTok{)), }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
 
  \CommentTok{\# Find product description}
\NormalTok{  description\_element }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{html\_node}\NormalTok{(div\_element, }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}span.a{-}size{-}base{-}plus.a{-}color{-}base.a{-}text{-}normal\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{  description }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{ifelse}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{!}\FunctionTok{is.na}\NormalTok{(description\_element), }\FunctionTok{html\_text}\NormalTok{(description\_element), }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
 
  \CommentTok{\# Find product price}
\NormalTok{  price\_element }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{html\_node}\NormalTok{(div\_element, }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}span.a{-}price{-}whole\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{  price }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{ifelse}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{!}\FunctionTok{is.na}\NormalTok{(price\_element), }\FunctionTok{html\_text}\NormalTok{(price\_element), }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
 
  \CommentTok{\# Find product ratings}
\NormalTok{  rating\_element }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{html\_node}\NormalTok{(div\_element, }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}span.a{-}icon{-}alt\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{  rating }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{ifelse}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{!}\FunctionTok{is.na}\NormalTok{(rating\_element), }\FunctionTok{html\_text}\NormalTok{(rating\_element), }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{  rating }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{gsub}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"out of 5 stars"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{""}\NormalTok{, rating, }\AttributeTok{fixed =} \ConstantTok{TRUE}\NormalTok{)}
 
  \CommentTok{\# Scrape reviews for each product}
\NormalTok{  reviews }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{character}\NormalTok{()}
  \ControlFlowTok{if}\NormalTok{ (link }\SpecialCharTok{!=} \StringTok{\textquotesingle{}\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{) \{}
    \CommentTok{\# Go to the reviews section of the product}
\NormalTok{    review\_url }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{paste0}\NormalTok{(link, }\StringTok{"\#customerReviews"}\NormalTok{)}
    \FunctionTok{tryCatch}\NormalTok{(\{}
\NormalTok{      review\_page }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{read\_html}\NormalTok{(review\_url)}
     
 
\NormalTok{      review\_elements }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{html\_nodes}\NormalTok{(review\_page, }\StringTok{\textquotesingle{}span[data{-}hook="review{-}body"] span\textquotesingle{}}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{      reviews }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{html\_text}\NormalTok{(review\_elements)}
     
      \CommentTok{\# Limit to the first 10 reviews}
\NormalTok{      reviews }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ reviews[}\DecValTok{1}\SpecialCharTok{:}\FunctionTok{min}\NormalTok{(}\DecValTok{10}\NormalTok{, }\FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(reviews))]}
\NormalTok{    \}, }\AttributeTok{error =} \ControlFlowTok{function}\NormalTok{(e) \{}
\NormalTok{      reviews }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{rep}\NormalTok{(}\ConstantTok{NA}\NormalTok{, }\DecValTok{10}\NormalTok{)  }\CommentTok{\# Fill with NAs if there\textquotesingle{}s no review}
\NormalTok{    \})}
\NormalTok{  \}}
 
  \CommentTok{\# Append product data and reviews to the list}
\NormalTok{  product\_data }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{append}\NormalTok{(product\_data, }\FunctionTok{list}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{data.frame}\NormalTok{(}
    \AttributeTok{Link =} \FunctionTok{rep}\NormalTok{(link, }\FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(reviews)),}
    \AttributeTok{Description =} \FunctionTok{rep}\NormalTok{(description, }\FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(reviews)),}
    \AttributeTok{Price =} \FunctionTok{rep}\NormalTok{(price, }\FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(reviews)),}
    \AttributeTok{Rating =} \FunctionTok{rep}\NormalTok{(rating, }\FunctionTok{length}\NormalTok{(reviews)),}
    \AttributeTok{Review =}\NormalTok{ reviews}
\NormalTok{  )))}
\NormalTok{\}}

\CommentTok{\# Combine all product data into one data frame}
\NormalTok{all\_reviews\_df }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{do.call}\NormalTok{(rbind, product\_data)}

\CommentTok{\# Save to CSV}
\FunctionTok{write.csv}\NormalTok{(all\_reviews\_df, }\StringTok{"automotive\_reviews.csv"}\NormalTok{, }\AttributeTok{row.names =} \ConstantTok{FALSE}\NormalTok{)}
\NormalTok{all\_reviews\_df}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

## 1                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           This is a pretty good and fast alternative to using a Swiffer duster or car cleaning wipes. This picked up the amount of dust that had collected the past year for me (I don't really drive, so not much dust). It's easy to use, grips well, you can see the dust collected on the gel. If you have a lot of dust, debris, crumbs galore, do not use this product first! This is not meant for cleaning really grimy cars. This is great for light layers, when you notice dust collecting. I agree with another reviewer saying it doesn't get into the vents very well, but if you have small enough fingers, it's easy to work the gel in between the slats. Also, do not store in the glove box. Think about it: your car is out in direct sunlight, facing the elements within your microclimate, so your car will heat up or cool down which will deteriorate the gel overtime even if stored in the glove box. Keep this somewhere inside your home, away from small children.

## 5                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         This stuff is a must have for me, it didn't take long to find this helpful and convenient to use. When I am finished driving for the day, routine is to take an extra 45 seconds and absorb all the dust, dirt, ashes, etc. from my dash and center console.I definitely ordered two more for on deck, and I feel, depending, that one of these gel slime will last a solid two months before it gets too grimy.Great case it stores in, which prolongs the use and just very convenient to store in car somewhere... preferably not in sunlight.As I mentioned, it is a slime type of gel, so with heavy use there is a extremely light residue left behind. But honestly it really is not an issue in even the least. Also if I very lightly absorb particles, the residue is pretty much non existent.I recommend highly for any surface tidying up you need, and hard to reach places. In a very slight way, this is a game changer.

## 7                                              I pruchased this to use in my vehicle to get into those hard to clean areas. I ended up using it in my dad's work truck to really put it to the test. He is working in a very dusty area with the red dirt....his truck was covered in the thick dust, so a perfect test of the product. He and I cleaned what we could with rags, but I wanted to try this stuff out on the creases and vents. It worked alright. Here are the pros/cons of the product from my initial test:Pros:- Ease of use: This is very easy to use. Just open it up, pull it out, and start dabbing it into the dusty areas. I found that tapping the dust to get the worst of it off before dragging it over a second time worked best.- Cleaning: This is good for loose dust. It worked really well at removing the dust in the vents and some of the corners you could not get a rag into.Cons:- Cleaning: This did not remove some of the stuck on dust that a rag would have removed. I also found that getting in tighter crevices did not work very well either. It also left a little greasy feel that may attract dust or that some people may not like on their dashes or inside their vehicles.- Cleaning the product: With as heavy of dust that was in my dad's truck, the gel got pretty dirty. I am not sure the best way to clean it, or if you can even clean it. Rags and towels are easy...just throw them into a washing machine. I'm guessing this is use until completely dirty and throw away.- Messy: This also leaves a greasy feel to your hands. With rags, you can usually minimize this, but this stuff gets all over your fingers, especially the finger you use to press it into vents.Overall, this is something that is a neat idea, but it really is not great. It worked okay at getting loose dirt and dust off of surfaces, but you could also get the same results from using something like tape or wrapping a small tool with some cloth and using cleaning agents. This might make a cheap, fun stocking stuffer if you want to get something that is different. Personally, I don't think I'll buy this again and just use rags.

## 15                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            I used the Airmoto Tire Inflator right away to put air in my car tires, and it worked just as expected. It's portable and works well for inflating car, motorcycle, and bicycle tires.The only suggestion I have for improvement is that the hose where you attach the compressor to the tire could be longer or positioned differently. ## 47                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           I've had a Slime Home Air Station (120 volt only) for many years, but the hose recently failed and couldn't be repaired, so it was time to find a replacement. This piece meets the need. It seems well-made and comes with a useful User Manual. However, it IS quite different from what I had before.First off, it's 12 volt only, via a standard auto 12V  socket. The User Manual said to start the car's engine while using it, so I'm guessing it draws a fair amount of current and might flatten your battery with prolonged use. The inflator hose is also much shorter than what I was used to, but still long enough to reach the valve-stem at the 12 o'clock position while the compressor remains on the ground. It's a bonus that it stays put when it's running and doesn't skate across the surface, as my old unit did.The built-in digital pressure gauge is easy to read, but reads about 2.5 PSI over actual pressure as checked by a separate calibrated  pressure gauge. Actual 35 PSI reads 37.5 PSI on this unit. Not really a big deal. If you can make change, you can do the math.The best feature is the Auto-stop at a preset pressure. My old unit did not have this, so I had to stare at the gauge for several minutes as the needle slowly crept up the dial. On this one, just set the desired pressure and start the compressor. The digital pressure gauge shows inflation progress 0.5 PSI at a time. When it hits the preset setting, it shuts off within a few seconds. My car has 235/55ZR20 tires and this unit will raise the pressure from 32 PSI to 38 PSI in about 3 minutes; not as fast as having a tank-type 120 volt 150 PSI compressor, but certainly acceptable for an occasional-use compact 12 volt unit. I paid less than $30 for this one with next day delivery, so I think qualifies as a great value. Highly recommended.

The pressure indicator seems accurate, which is a critical feature when inflating tires.Pros:Lightweight and compact design makes it easy to store and handle.Long cord provides excellent reach, especially for larger vehicles like a Jeep.Accurate pressure indicator for reliable readings.Cons:The connector occasionally slips out of the cigarette lighter socket during use, which can be a bit annoying.After about 10 minutes of use, the connector and hose become quite hot, which might raise durability concerns with prolonged operation.Real-world performance:I tested the compressor on my Jeep's 225/65R17 tires, inflating them from 19 PSI to 35 PSI. ## 74                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Im probably like you, and figured, yeah, they say its going to do all these great things and itll probably not work anywhere near as advertised. Oh boy was I wrong about that.This product is quite frankly amazing. Its very easy to use and doesnt take hours and hours. Everything you need is in the kit except masking tape, which I would highly recommend you use to tape off the perimeter of your light so you dont get any of the coating on your car paint or accidentally hit it with the sand paper.You first use the oxidizer remover, wipe and clean that off, then you go to the 1000 and 2000 grit sanding discs. Get a good spray bottle with nice clean water, keep the headlight wet while youre sanding it because basically what youre doing is wet sanding the surface. You can actually feel the sandpaper, engaging the scratches, and when you finally have a nice smooth, feel to it, spray it down and wipe it off and clean it with a microfiber cloth. Then apply the coating. When you apply the coating, it is literally a miracle. How perfect and clean and clear the lens becomes. It looks brand freaking new!I literally was walking around the garage looking at it saying damn that looks good, damn that looks good! You will not be disappointed. This is one of the best products to come around in a long, long time and is worth every penny. I even had a little extra left over and did my cub cadet headlight cover.

## 128                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Helps with car trunk organizer. Can hold a variety of items. Helps me to keep things in one place. Happy with the product. Can fold when not in use. Nice size.

## 130                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               The Good:The Velcro side strap are nice for shrinking to 2 or 1 compartment.  The netting is set up to separate more items into smaller pockets. Price is on the economy level. Compartments collapse down well. If you are never taking this out of your car, then it is probably worth it when you can get it on a discount.The Bad:The side walls and pockets are paper thin and flimsy, you most certainly don't get the padded and stiff side walls or pockets that are pictured.  When you go to move or shift anything, the entire compartment does an accordian-like shift due to there being no side support like in competitor items (see x-cosrack trunk organizer). The other big flaw is that the handles are only on the inside of the compartments on either end, so if you taper it down to 2 compartments and you bought a 3 compartment one, based on the weight, you may be in for a surprise when going to move something like heavy-ish groceries indoors.Conclusion:I'd spend an extra $10-15 on one of the nicer organizers that have small helpful extras like straps to keep the bags in place or small coolers. They aren't going to be anything overly impressive, but they may do things like keep bad fish and leftover smells from permeating the inside of your car if you can't make it straight home right away(Yes, this happened and I forgot until I opened that bag and was slapped across the face by smelly fried Cod).  Hope this helps!

                                                                                                                                         Huggies wipes have quickly become a must-have in our household! With Huggies wipes you just get one every time. They are loosely attached and separate easily when pulled out. The next wipe is easy to grab and again, you only get one each time. ## 11                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  I recently purchased a pack of Huggies diapers for my little one, and I am thrilled with the quality and performance of these diapers. Huggies has always been a trusted brand when it comes to baby care, and these diapers have certainly lived up to their reputation.First and foremost, the fit of these diapers is excellent. They are designed with a snug and comfortable fit that keeps my baby dry and secure. The elastic waistband and stretchy sides ensure a proper fit without any leaks or discomfort. I appreciate how these diapers adapt to my baby's movements, providing a secure and flexible fit throughout the day.The absorbency of Huggies diapers is outstanding. They are equipped with a highly effective absorbent core that quickly locks away wetness, keeping my baby's skin dry and rash-free. Even during overnight use, these diapers have proven to be reliable in preventing leaks and maintaining dryness. This gives me peace of mind knowing that my baby is comfortable and protected.I also appreciate the breathability of these diapers. The materials used are soft and breathable, allowing for proper airflow and preventing any irritation or diaper rash. This is especially important for my baby's sensitive skin, and Huggies diapers have proven to be gentle and non-irritating.The design of these diapers is also adorable. The fun and colorful prints add a touch of cuteness to my baby's outfit. It's a small detail, but it definitely adds to the overall positive experience of using these diapers.Furthermore, the packaging of Huggies diapers is convenient and user-friendly. The resealable tabs make it easy to open and close, ensuring that the diapers stay fresh and organized. The clear size indicators on the packaging also make it simple to find the right size for my growing baby.Lastly, I appreciate the availability and affordability of Huggies diapers. They are readily available in most stores and online, making it convenient for me to purchase them whenever needed. Considering the quality and performance they offer, I find these diapers to be reasonably priced and a great value for money.In conclusion, I highly recommend Huggies diapers to any parent or caregiver. Their excellent fit, superb absorbency, breathability, and adorable design make them a top choice for keeping your baby dry, comfortable, and happy. With their convenient packaging and affordability, Huggies diapers have become a staple in my baby care routine, and I am extremely satisfied with my purchase.

## 14         I'VE BEEN USING THIS PARTICULAR HUGGIES WIPES FOR SEVERAL YEARS. I used to use a different brand of wipes. But after a couple of years of buying them, the manufacturer went cheap and changed the material to such an inferrior cloth, that the material would fall apart and leave a bunch of loose cotton all over your skin. NOT GOOD. Becuase now you have to actually wash it off. That's when I switched to Huggies, and have been using them for at least five (5) years.MANY USAGES:I take these wipes with me everywhere, because you never know when you'll need them. And particularly in the Summer, when it's hot and muggy out; I use them to clean and cool off my face, arms and legs, etc... And no matter where I am, when I'm away from home, I always run into moms who needs one for her child. These wipes  come in handy for cleaning faces and hands after a meal, while on the run or at home.TEXTURE:These wipes are sturdy and easy to manage with one hand. Their more than just wipes, their like wash cloths. They don't fall apart, their super soft, and have enough moisture in them to clean your parts effectively. The package says their hypoallergenic, and I believe it, because my family have been using this brand for many years, and no one has broken out from them. We love them, especially for the bathroom.LIKE WASHING WITH WATER:Another good use is using the wipes like your're washing your hands with water.  I carry a wad of these wipes with me when on the go, so when I'm away from home and really need to give my hands a wash, I just squeeze the soapy water out the wipe into my hand and rub both hands together, as if to be washing my hands with soap and water. Then I use the wipe to finish the job. Works every time.EASY TO OPEN FLIP-TOP:I like this brand of Huggies for many reasons, and the easy flip top was one of the main reasons I keep coming back. You can actually flip the top open and closed with one hand, which I do frequently. So, that's a feature that comes in handy when I don't have both hands available.PRICE IS COST EFFECTIVE:As you know, wipes can be very expenseive; $4, $5 or more just for one pack, and not get many wipes either. Many times the local store runs out of the brand you like, and you're stuck paying a lot of money for a small pack and a brand you're not familiar with. This particular item of Huggies, sold on Amazon comes in a  bundle of 11 flip-top packs, so you'll have plenty on hand for a long time. AND THE PRICE IS GREAT, TOO; I bought this item in October 2023, and paid less than $19 dollars, including taxes. With 11 packs in the bundle, that makes the average price for one pack less than $2 bucks!RECOMMEND?: Absolutely! I recommend this item to anyone who wants a wipe thats super soft, hypoallergenic, has lots of soap and water and cleans like a wash cloth. Oh, the size is great too!

## 60                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Ive been using this product for about a year now in my home office. I was desperate to drown out the incessant barking from a next door neighbors dog so I could concentrate on work. Im also on the phone a lot and didnt want the dog to be heard in the background. We did try talking to our neighbor about the dog, which had minimal effect. Since using this device, my stress level has gone way down and I am much less distracted. This tiny little machine packs a big punch! It can get REALLY loud, but Ive figured out the ideal volume for me (about halfway up) and that, combined with my bluetooth ear piece which reduces background noise, ensures I can have professional phone calls again and no one has ever mentioned they cant hear me. The device also helps when my son is home from school on a break and wont stop yelling at his video game in the basement (haha). At first, I felt resentful that due to my inconsiderate neighbor, I had to purchase this device, but now Ive gotten so used to it I barely think about it anymore. Its the first thing I turn on after hitting the light switch when I go into my office each morning. In fact, I love it so much I just purchased a second one for my husband to use in the basement, when the dog starts going off. Its so affordable, I may eventually end up getting one for every room in the house. It also blocks out loud construction noises and other annoying environmental sounds. It does begin to auto-shut off after about 2 hrs (not sure if thats a built in feature or if I could somehow bypass it), but once I notice the sound decreasing, I just hit the power button and its another 2 hrs of being in my peaceful cocoon.

## 66  One of the best items I've ever spent money on. I was having trouble sleeping at one point, and for a while would turn the fan on in my bathroom and let it run all night, to provide white noise, and also to block out the repetitive sounds my senior dog makes lol. (For context, she is very old and had some teeth pulled, so she smacks her mouth and lips a lot. She also can get anxious sometimes and likes to lick her bed, apparently it helps soothe her. None of that is her fought and I don't hold it against her, but as you can imagine, the sounds are not the greatest thing to hear when trying to fall asleep haha.) Anyways, I'm a very worrisome person and I began to get paranoid that leaving my bathroom fan on all night could be a potential fire hazard. So I stopped using it and began looking into noise machines. I looked at so many different kinds and eventually settled on this one. It ended up being perfect and is everything I wanted, plus more.Some cool features: You can change the timer for how long it stays on, or set it to just run all night, which is my go to setting. If you do set a timer, the white noise it creates doesn't just stop suddenly, it slowly fades out so not to disturb your sleep, which I think is a really cool part of its design. The volume buttons are easy to locate and do exactly what they're supposed to do. It also has a plethora of different sounds to use. My most favorite is the sound of heavy rain fall. I also use the bathroom fan sound quite a lot as well. Another feature I like is that it doesn't have a ton of bright lights on it. If you choose to turn the timer on, it will show a very faint dot based on which timer you pick. Because I let it run all night, there aren't any faint dots that show up. It's also very travel friendly, very similar to tossing a phone in your bag with its charger and walking out the door. I'll most likely buy a second one in the upcoming months for when I travel, that way my other one can stay at home. As far as sound quality goes, I give this noise machine a 10/10. The noises aren't scratchy or grating, but very natural and soothing. I've not had any issues with the volume or adjusting it and the speaker sounds great too.This little box has been a game changer for me in terms of falling asleep more easily, and I'm really glad I purchased it. If you're worried about it being complicated to use, don't be. It's super easy to setup, and basically plug and play. I've said it already, but I'm really happy with this purchase and it's definitely one of the best items I've spent money on. It's a quality item at a reasonable price and I couldn't be happier with it.Please Note: I was not paid to write this review. I was not given free merchandise to write this review. I wrote this review solely because I enjoyed this product and am very happy with my purchase.

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 I've been hesitant to get a digital frame because the setup and ongoing maintenance sounded exhausting. This was pretty out the box and easy to use, thankfully.Pros:- The picture quality is great, and nothing is pixelated long as your photos are at least 1200x1800 (but even then, I've got old photos that still show up well)- Option to fit to frame or original size if they're cropped is nice, and the background adjusts to blurred behind it- The frame auto orients to portrait or landscape depending on how you want to stand it up- Sleep function so it turns off during night hours is great to reduce light pollution- Option to display clock in 12 or 24hr format- Slot for USD stick or SD card if you want to keep local storage of photos instead of storing in the cloud on the app.Cons:- The app takes some getting used to. It can only upload 8-9 photos at a time, otherwise it prompts you to bilk upload (but then you can't edit each size manually). First time I did a bulk upload, it picked up other photos I did not select, so, not sure what's going on there.- My hesitancy with using any tech that has an app (especially from a 3rd party and not a major known brand) is that it's likely to fall into disuse, the developers will probably stop updating it eventually, and it will be obsolete. I'm glad there's local storage on it to address when that will eventually probably happen, and this wasn't expensive, so not an immediate issue, but something to keep in mind for any device that comes with a propietary app.

## 7                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       This frame looks really nice and does a good job trying to look like a traditional wooden frame. I do like that this particular frame has worked well so far. The picture quality is good but it also depends on the quality of the photo. It does not do anything too crazy in terms of enhancing the picture quality so be aware of that. Regardless of that, I do like this digital photo frame. You are able to rotate it as needed. It does not have the traditional frame holder that pops out of the back. It is just a simple screw on plastic piece. The angle cannot be adjusted unfortunately. You are able to mount this on a desktop monitor mount which is interesting. There are also holds to mount this on the wall as needed. You just need to be aware that this device does not come with a hanging aid so it can be hard to mount for some. There is internal memory and I do love that you are able to transmit the picture to easily share the photo directly from your phone as needed. You are also able to install a USB flash drive or an SD card if you want more memory but you are allocated 32 gb of memory as needed. I am able to share easily all my current photos in one picture frame and just have it rotate through different pictures to show all my different pictures. I got this because I am limited on space in my home so I cannot have a bunch of photos frames so this is something that could show all my pictures family and travels. In terms of feel, the photo frame tries to mimic the wood like finish but it is a solid plastic frame from what I can tell. It has a smoother feel. The color is pretty dark so it is not really that great for the brighter rooms. The frame is pretty strong so it should not break very easily. The paint is put on well so you do not have to worry about any flaking or chipping. The screen is pretty sturdy. I am unsure if it is temper glass or strong plastic but it is responsive. The responsiveness of the screen. I am wondering why it utilize a monitor mount style hole in order to mount a certain way. It does come with a screen cover you need to remove. It runs a very simple to use operating system so you do not have to worry about not being able to use it. It can play all the pictures you want but the thing you need to make sure is that the pictures are same resolution and such. For the most part, it is pretty much plug any play. It can read an SD card. It does not have to be formatted from what I can tell.  It does come with a power outlet and I did not try to see if this can run on a portable battery but it is harder to hide the cable if you are hanging this on your wall. The transition between photos seem to move pretty fluently through. It does not get warm. Overall this is a decent smart photo frame to have. The wood looks good for the rustic decorum and it is well painted / made frame. It tries to mimic the photo frame as best they can. The touch screen is nice. The application could be better though.

## 24                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          I wanted to buy another laptop for work purposes but also be useful for travelling and for gaming so I saw this laptop for sale during Black Friday! Excellent purchase! Here is my pros and cons after a week of owning this:Con:1. 1920 x 1200 FHD 165Hz Display is very much an downgrade against my Legion 5 Pro 16" 2560 x 1600 IPS LCD 165Hz Display... But I guess with the parts offered, ASUS had to make some budget cuts somewhere I guess... (for the model I've chosen and not wanting to spend more than $1500 USD).2. Automatic MUX Switching is annoying... it optimizes which option to best suit for your current usage at the time (e.g. if you ran an game vs closing the game and brings you to the desktop). The automatic switch seems like its great and all but it ruins the display setting and when an game is playing, it switches again and sends you back to the desktop and ruins the display setting/resolution once more... Its best to just set it on the dedicated GPU option so you dont have to deal with this...3. Standard SSD Capacity is too low (again with cost saving measures but literally everyone these days just buy additional SSD stick anyways)... so snagged an SK.Hynix P41 SSD 2TB stick on sale to manually install for loading heavy application and games on there; really easy to install and easy to unscrew the back; there is an empty NVMe Gen4 M.2 2280 slot for you to install your SSDWorks Great after installing correctly and no Issues now! (make sure after install of SSD, just load into Windows and open up disk management to reformat (quick format! never full on SSD!) No need to tinker with BIOS setting...Do not tighten the SSD screws too much where the stick bends! thats incorrect! screw in ever so slightly so that the stick itself wont lodge out or move at all.Pros:1. RTX 4060 8GB - 140W Max TGP2. i7-13650HX - beats my Ryzen-7 5800H on my Legion 5 Pro3. RGB bar looks awesome!4. Battery 90WhNeutral:1. RGB Keys - heard mixed reviews on ASUS's design on this; of course, the Legion 5 RGB keyboard design is the best of the best but this is just okay and its not too bad in my eyes.2. Same weight and nearly the same dimensions as my Legion 5 Pro so portability is the same-ish but way better than my old MSI gaming laptop from 2017 where you can put this in your backpack and still have room to put other accessories and such.This is all I've noticed currently but either way, its a great mid-tier gaming laptop! I can run cyberpunk all max setting without issues or framerate drops and every other AAA game titles up to this point... This laptop should last an long time until AAA games becomes more graphically intense and requiring more processing power... but again this is the best you can get for your money and highly recommend!

I was a little hesitant to pull the trigger because of some of the reviewers on here saying they got a terrible renewed iPad... I can assure you that the one that I received was in overall 4.5/5 condition. The screen looked brand new, and even the rest of the body didn't appear to have any sort of defects. The cellular connection I'm getting (Ting Mobile, baby) is as steady as my cell phone (I was a little worried that the cell antenna in these wouldn't be of great quality, but I'm happy to say it is.)I've never owned any iPads, but recently got an iPhone and chose this over other tablets because I know Apple retina displays are actually very nice. Colors come across as vivid. Resolution turned up to the point where you're really struggling to make out individual pixels, and the screen is bright enough that I'm not struggling to see this in the car. And I bought this because I wanted a nice, big screen to look at when I'm in the car. One note about the display - it's a 4:3 display rather than the more contemporary 16:9 displays of the Android tablet world. That makes this about a ~9"-9.3" display when watching content with a 1.777:1 or 1.85:1 aspect ratio which are the standard aspect ratios for films/TV shows (which is why your TV at home is a 16:9 aspect ratio!) Back to car use, the GPS works very well alongside cellular data. There are some cool navigation apps available on Apple, plus now I don't feel left out when there's other neat apps for Apple that I can't get on my Android phone. Also there are actually so many good accessories available for this thing because Apple has a small product line in comparison to the dozens of Android tablets and phones coming out each year from numerous manufacturers which equals lots of accessories with not so many reviews.I chose this specific model because it's the newest cellular Apple tablet at this price point. As of now, it's about 2-3 years old. The other ones I found on Amazon around the $200-300 range were as old as 8 years and without cellular, which is why I spent the extra money for something like this. I am happier than I was when I made my impulse buy which is impressive. You really do get a lot of tech for the money. A new 64gb iPad 10.2 with cellular is $459. This is only 32gb, and with a fresh install of iOS you get 23gb available to you. A little worried it won't be enough for me, but I'll probably manage.My only con so far is that the battery had a weird glitch. When you're in a high state of charge, it seems to be discharging at a slow enough rate. I got down to around 40% after using it for about 4 hours after using it to stream Hulu using cell data with full brightness. Then while using it with GPS on and streaming Spotify with full brightness on, it jumped from about 35% down to 20% within a few minutes. I can't complain too much because this is a 3 year old device about 2/3rds the price of new.I got mine from the seller "techexchangee" - came with a 5v/2.4a charger (or 12 watt) charger plus cable. Shipped in a plain box with lots of bubble wrap. Again, from the outside, I wouldn't have been able to tell it was renewed.P.S. On Amazon, I found a tablet mount for a car using a CD player and that thing is great. Highly recommend that if you want to use this in a car. It's the "APPS2CAR universal car mount CD slot" for $20.

                                                                                      This Taygeer Carry-on Backpack is everything I needed and more! Its also super comfortable to wear, even when packed full. Whether for a weekend trip, college, or the gym, this bag is perfect. Highly recommend it as a gift or for personal use!

## 9                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Update #2 - Ordered a second one for my 14 year old granddaughter. Once she saw mine, she wanted one. Had ordered her a different style and color, which Id thought would be a better fit for her needs. Amazon filled the order, and not only shopped a totally different style but also color. Id ordered a pretty light blue because the pink in that companys suitcase style backpack was a gaudy neon pink, the color they shipped was an ugly brownish grey. She was very disappointed, but is such a good kid would have kept it so I wouldnt feel bad. Her dad is the one who told me. So I ordered her this pink backpack. Its arrived and she is much happier. Funny that a 14 year old kid wanted a copy of the same backpack her 78 year old grandma has. As for the ugly one, my husband is happier to carry that color around than a pink one.As for Amazon substituting a completely different style and color for something that was a gift without first letting me know, I am not pleased with them at all.Update:  Used this backpack on a recent flight to visit family. It was exactly what we needed. Flew American Airlines, and it fit under the seat in front of me. It was full but not stuffed.  I put it where the bottom faced toward the front of the plane and the handle at the top of the backpack faced me. That way it was easy to grab hold of and pull out from under the seat. I put a bunch of clothes in a packing cube on the bottom of the backpack with toiletries in 2 zip lock bags plus my purse on top, near the handle. That left my electronics, papers, tickets, ID, and some basic purse type stuff in the zippered pocket in front. Everything fit well, and the packed backpack was much lighter and more comfortable to carry than my previous backpack. Plus it fit under the seat better. As for the pink getting dirty, the little bit that was on it wiped right off.Also, when I showed how this new backpack opens to our 14 and 15 year old granddaughters, they both wanted one. So I ordered a couple more for them. They each travel to their other parents homes whenever there is a school break, and like how much easier it will be to access things in the larger storage area. Plus they can pack more clothes. Also, both go out of town occasionally for sports events and these will be great for those times. I dont think they will keep there regular backpacks for school, and use these for overnights with friends and traveling. I also showed my backpack to a couple of adults, and they were as equally impressed.Favorite feature is it opens like a suitcase. Provides so much more usable space that way. And so much easier to access. Least favorite feature is the zip area for electronics could be better designed and have a little more protective padding. It could have had better pocket design to hold purse type items, to help eliminate the need to also carry a purse. My old backpack has a much more practical design for that, even though it provides about the same amount of space. Also, the inner pockets are done with cheaper quality materials.That said, I still prefer this one. It can easily be adjusted to my 52 frame, is lighter in weight which my 78 year old body appreciates, opens up completely so easier to put my packing cubes in, easier for airport security to search if necessary, easier to adjust the items inside and secure so they dont all slide to the bottom, and the color scheme will make it easier to identify if included with a bunch of other pieces of luggage. My 80 year old husband even admits that he will be willing to carry it for me as it isnt really pink but more a beige color.  If our granddaughters didnt already have a lot of backpacks, I would have ordered them each one. Yes, I definitely recommend it.

## 16                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            I've had--and still have--many, many backpacks; been buying them since high school, and I buy a new one every few years. I purchased this one in part because it will fit my 17" laptop, but also because I needed something to replace my old and ratty "day to day" backpack for "urban schlepping."  By and large, this is one very sturdy, spacious and versatile backpack, perhaps the best one I've ever bought. It arrived at my place of work with a whole bunch of other stuff I had ordered on Amazon; for the trip home, I was able to stuff my old (partially filled) backpack into it, along with two packaged tablecloths, two shower curtain liners, and several other smaller items--it all fit very easily with little packing effort expended. Two days later I fit 25 lbs of groceries into it, again with ease, and with room to spare--didn't even need the zippered side pockets, but I probably could have put another couple pounds worth of stuff in them. Both times, both trips, I found that the loaded pack rode very nicely, very comfortably near the center of my back, and that was without having yet made any adjustments to the straps. The cushioning on the back-facing side of the backpack is generous but not overly so, and yeah, the "airflow" feature between the two cushioned areas does seem to aid in the comfort factor. The straps are amply wide, also padded, and they have a measure of elasticity to them--near the top of each strap is a trapezoidal-shaped (2x2x3) of sturdy, "one way" stretch material (stretches vertically, not horizontally); when carrying the groceries, the pack didn't "bounce around" or anything, but the elastic acted like a shock absorber of sorts, made for flexibility in movement and kept the top of the straps from digging into my shoulders as other backpacks with heavy loads have done in the past. Overall, the main material is thick and obviously strong, the exterior front pockets are conveniently, smartly placed; the zippers are all seem very strong and reliable; and the stitching of the seams and strap connections appears to be very solidly done. When first looking at this bag, I thought I might be put off by the solid plastic handle at the top of the front compartment--never had bag with one of those--but I've already come to appreciate it: while on the subway I had to take the pack off and carry it by the handle and it allowed for a very good and solid grip, like carrying piece of luggage; also, while wearing the pack the handle doesn't interfere with my head movements at all like I thought it might--doesn't even come near my head. If I have any complaints at all, I'd say I'd prefer that the "organizer pocket" on the bottom front to have a bit stiffer accessory sleeve within (where you put pens and whatnot), but I'm sure I can deal with what's there, or perhaps I'll  invest in a small organizer or "catchall" to slip in there. Folks, this is a real good back pack; it might be overkill if you're looking for something just to carry a few light items all the time, but if you need something that will stand up to the regular (or even occasional) heavy load, or to maybe use as a carry on travel bag, this sucker is it.Just as a side note, perhaps to illustrate how sturdy this bag is:  A few days after getting the backpack, I was watching a 60 Minutes segment on "Gorilla Doctors," veterinarians who traipse deep into the jungle to aid gorillas in peril. While in the field attending one anesthetized gorilla who had been snared, they show the vets unpacking their gear and medicines and whatnot . . . and the lead vet had what appeared to be this exact backpack. So, if jungle docs have confidence in this bag . . . go for it.

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The SwissGear 1900 Scansmart TSA 17-Inch Backpack is a highly functional and durable choice for travelers, commuters, and students. Its spacious design comfortably fits a 17-inch laptop, while the ScanSmart technology allows for quick and hassle-free TSA checkpoint clearance without removing the laptop. The backpack features multiple compartments for organization, including dedicated spaces for tablets, chargers, and other essentials. Its rugged construction, reinforced zippers, and weather-resistant material ensure it can withstand daily wear and tear. With padded shoulder straps and a breathable back panel, its comfortable for extended use. This backpack is a reliable and efficient option for anyone needing both style and practicality.

## 20
